{"id":"cmd_clear","label":"/clear — start a new conversation with EMPTY context (aliases /reset, /new)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"code.claude.com_docs_en_commands.md","source_location":"L63","source_url":"https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands","captured_at":"2026-07-22","author":null,"contributor":null},
{"id":"cmd_compact","label":"/compact — free up context while CONTINUING the same conversation","file_type":"concept","source_file":"code.claude.com_docs_en_commands.md","source_location":"L63","source_url":"https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands","captured_at":"2026-07-22","author":null,"contributor":null},
{"id":"cmd_branch","label":"/branch [name] — branch the conversation and SWITCH INTO it (foreground); preserves the original (return via /resume)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"code.claude.com_docs_en_commands.md","source_location":"L57","source_url":"https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands","captured_at":"2026-07-22","author":null,"contributor":null},
{"id":"cmd_fork","label":"/fork [prompt] — copy the conversation into a NEW independent BACKGROUND SESSION (inherits everything up to now); keep working here (v2.1.212+)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"code.claude.com_docs_en_commands.md","source_location":"L86","source_url":"https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands","captured_at":"2026-07-22","author":null,"contributor":null},
{"id":"cmd_subtask","label":"/subtask <task> — spawn a FORKED SUBAGENT that INHERITS the full conversation, runs in the background, and reports its result back into this conversation (v2.1.212+)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"code.claude.com_docs_en_commands.md","source_location":"L137","source_url":"https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands","captured_at":"2026-07-22","author":null,"contributor":null},
{"id":"cmd_background","label":"/background [prompt] — detach the current session to run as a background agent, freeing the terminal (alias /bg)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"code.claude.com_docs_en_commands.md","source_location":"L55","source_url":"https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands","captured_at":"2026-07-22","author":null,"contributor":null},
{"id":"cmd_resume","label":"/resume — return to an earlier conversation (or the pre-branch/pre-clear original)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"code.claude.com_docs_en_commands.md","source_location":"L29","source_url":"https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands","captured_at":"2026-07-22","author":null,"contributor":null},
{"id":"insight_command_context_inheritance","label":"Context model: /clear = EMPTY context; /compact = shrink-in-place same convo; /branch = foreground copy you switch into; /fork = independent background-session copy; /subtask = forked subagent that INHERITS full convo + reports back. Both /subtask and /fork INHERIT context — neither is a reset like /clear. (v2.1.212+; pre-2.1.212 /subtask==/fork==forked-subagent)","file_type":"rationale","source_file":"code.claude.com_docs_en_commands.md","source_location":"L29-L137","source_url":"https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands","captured_at":"2026-07-22","author":null,"contributor":null},
{"id":"insight_autonomy_delegation","label":"For autonomous multi-phase work: /subtask backgrounds a task that reports back (no babysitting) but carries full context; the Agent TOOL gives FRESH-context subagents (lean); a Workflow pipelines fresh subagents resumably. /clear+resume is the only true context RESET but needs a human paste.","file_type":"rationale","source_file":"code.claude.com_docs_en_commands.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://code.claude.com/docs/en/commands","captured_at":"2026-07-22","author":null,"contributor":null}
